'use strict';(function(){const indexCfg={cache:true};indexCfg.doc={id:'id',field:['title','content'],store:['title','href','section'],};const index=FlexSearch.create('balance',indexCfg);window.bookSearchIndex=index;index.add({'id':0,'href':'/docs/-example/','title':"About Me",'section':"Docs",'content':"Hiiiiii______!!! Nice to meet you! #   Hi there! My name is Alexa Cheng, I am an Industrial Design student from Donghua University. I growed up in southern China where there used to be lots of forest and plant resources, so I’m a huge fan in technology, biology and nature protection aspects issues. I admire Neri Oxman’s work very much, and I’m now self-learning generative art and creative coding; I like Product System Design, the issue recently that I’ve being thinking is about how to make proper strategy in order to maximize a product’s value within the whole product system. I hope one day I will achieve my goal — to integrate my professional knowledge into social aspects like ecological protection and public welfare, to generate greater value for the society.     "});index.add({'id':2,'href':'/docs/-Experienments/Intimate-Law/','title':"Intimate Law",'section':"Experienments",'content':"Intimate Law #  The law and principle are always something which seems to be hard to get close to. Like the legislation, the rule of human society, the principle of social order which you cannot violate. Horrible terrifying. While this law, if we use a different perspective to see, in nature growth and human body evolution, what you can see is the sequence of gene. It’s soft and intimate while it’s also called” law”.\nSo what is am considering is whether we can use these natural tools to reshape our social order, redefine the concept and make it more visible?\n How to combine the nature language together with human society to make the world more intimate? Can we use the color pigment changes to show our emotion?\n  Get Home  Contribute  "});index.add({'id':3,'href':'/docs/-Experienments/The-Fictional/','title':"The Fictional",'section':"Experienments",'content':"The Fictional #  Some fiction sketches I did, trying to seek for the promising future together with the possible co-existence of fine art, advanced technology, visible morality and architecture. What could be human\u0026rsquo;s life be like in the next 500 years?\nWe are all familiar with Jules Gabriel Verne \u0026rsquo;s wonderful science fiction novels, we often regard these as \u0026ldquo;impossible\u0026rdquo; scenarios. But these novels also provide people with a bunch of possibilities of living under different conditions, fighting with their own weakness and in pursuit for self-evolution.\n \u0026lt; the Modern City \u0026gt; 2017  \u0026lt; Killing the Nightmare \u0026gt; 2019   \u0026lt; The last desert \u0026gt; 2020  \u0026lt; Purity \u0026gt; 2018  \u0026lt; BIO \u0026gt; 2020  \u0026lt; sculpture \u0026gt; 2020  \u0026lt; Iceberg \u0026gt; 2020 "});index.add({'id':5,'href':'/docs/-Projects/Bread-2018/','title':"Bread 2018",'section':"Projects",'content':"BRead #  BRead is an art and culture communication platform that brings audience, artists and curators together to lessen the distance between ordinary people and elegant art experiences. Inspired by the famous German artist Joseph Beuys: “Every man is an artist.” He believes that art comes from life and should return to life. How- ever, in contrast to the great division between art and life today, many people think that art is only something which the high-class people can afford.\n  "});index.add({'id':6,'href':'/docs/-Projects/Dumpling-2019/','title':"Dumpling 2019",'section':"Projects",'content':"Dumpling #  Side Pocket is an app platform made for booking laboratories online. It can improve and simplify the rental process to achieve more efficient communication between user and the administrator, students and teachers.\n  "});index.add({'id':7,'href':'/docs/-Projects/Narcissus-2017/','title':"Narcissus 2017",'section':"Projects",'content':"Narcissus tableware #  An experienmental projects which was inspired by nature growth. We tried to combined the tableware design together with the nature plant curving forms, to find some more new possibilities.\n "});index.add({'id':8,'href':'/docs/-Projects/Paperboat-2019/','title':"Paperboat 2019",'section':"Projects",'content':"Paperboat Action #  The “Paperboat Action” is an activity planned and designed by our group members by using Design Thinking methods after carrying a one-month research in a migrant children school, targeting at promoting “Quality Education”, one of the United Nation’s 17 sustainable development goals.\nEquality in education has always been a highly contro- versial topic, recently the United Nation has just proposed 17 sustainable development goals, one of which is ‘Quality Education’ . However,in China,the giant disparity between the rich and poor has led to significantly large inequlity in education.\n   We did a lot research work and composed them into a short video, check it here. This Video  "});index.add({'id':9,'href':'/docs/-Projects/Sidepocket-2018/','title':"Sidepocket 2018",'section':"Projects",'content':"Side Pocket #  The online lab reservation system in our school was really poor designed and annoying. The students who want to use lab have to reserve online from an online platform, while they’ve complained many times for its poor work flow structure design and invisible reviewing status.\nIn order to slove this problem, I designed the app Side Pocket. It is an online platform made for booking laboratories, equipements online. It can improve and simplify the rental process to achieve more efficient communication between user and the administrator, students and teachers.\n  Example #  Left Content Lorem markdownum insigne. Olympo signis Delphis! Retexi Nereius nova develat stringit, frustra Saturnius uteroque inter! Oculis non ritibus Telethusa protulit, sed sed aere valvis inhaesuro Pallas animam: qui quid, ignes. Miseratus fonte Ditis conubia.  Mid Content Lorem markdownum insigne. Olympo signis Delphis! Retexi Nereius nova develat stringit, frustra Saturnius uteroque inter!  Right Content Lorem markdownum insigne. Olympo signis Delphis! Retexi Nereius nova develat stringit, frustra Saturnius uteroque inter! Oculis non ritibus Telethusa protulit, sed sed aere valvis inhaesuro Pallas animam: qui quid, ignes. Miseratus fonte Ditis conubia.   "});index.add({'id':10,'href':'/docs/-Projects/Weed-2020/','title':"Weed 2020",'section':"Projects",'content':"Weed #  Weed is an easy-charging lighting product which aims at “providing users with agile and convenient lighting”. At the same time, by using the traditional Chinese imagery it arises people’s emotions towards nature and connects this feeling together with people’s daily lives.\n      Check more about this project here!\nThis Video  "});index.add({'id':11,'href':'/docs/Contact/','title':"Contact",'section':"Docs",'content':"Feel free to contact me!\nemail: alexacheng331@gmail.com cjy_lea331@yeah.net\nphone: 0086 13913306109, Mainland China\naddress: Shanghai, China\n"});})();